    "comment": {
      "brief": "Specifies a policy to control the loading and unloading of the image. The two common policies are `PreloadRetain`, the default which loads images at startup and keeps them loaded, and `UnloadUnused` which keeps only used images loaded.",
      "full": "Specifies a policy to control the loading and unloading of the image. The two common policies are `PreloadRetain`, the default which loads images at startup and keeps them loaded, and `UnloadUnused` which keeps only used images loaded.\n\nFor dynamic images, such as those coming from HTTP, you should use the `UnloadUnused` policy, otherwise you'll continue to consume more memory as more images are loaded. For example:\n\n    <Image Url=\"{imageLocation}\" MemoryPolicy=\"UnloadUnused\"/>"
    }
